This paper is about multi-objective query optimization (MOQO) in the context of databases, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also proposes approximation schemes for MOQO, which involves algorithm design and optimization, making it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper presents experimental results and extends the Postgres optimizer, which involves implementation and software engineering, making it relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and analysis of cost functions, which is relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
